"title": "8228: discernment, examples of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8228",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Perfect discernment is displayed by God and Jesus Christ. Evil spirits also have discernment, about the person and work of Christ. Discernment has been evident in the rulers and spiritual leaders of God's people, but Israel, like children and the foolish who lack judgment, failed to discern God's purpose and truth.</p>\n<h2>God's discernment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:1-Ps139:4\">PSA 139:1–139:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:4\">JOB 31:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job34:21\">JOB 34:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:13\">HEB 4:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:20\">1JN 3:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:12\">PSA 19:12</a> <em>God alone knows our hidden faults.</em></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's discernment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:25\">JHN 2:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:4\">MAT 9:4</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:8\">MRK 2:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:22\">LUK 5:22</a> <em>Jesus Christ discerns the thoughts of the teachers of the law</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:23\">MAT 16:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:33\">MRK 8:33</a> <em>Jesus Christ discerns the source of Peter's words</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:18\">MAT 22:18</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:15\">MRK 12:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:23\">LUK 20:23</a> <em>Jesus Christ discerns the true motive of his questioners</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:47\">JHN 1:47</a> <em>Jesus Christ sees into the heart of Nathaniel</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:16\">JHN 8:16</a> <em>Jesus Christ has perfect discernment of right and wrong.</em></p>\n<h2>Evil spirits' discernment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:23-Mark1:24\">MRK 1:23–1:24</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:33-Luke4:34\">LUK 4:33–4:34</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:34\">MRK 1:34</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:41\">LUK 4:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:17\">ACT 16:17</a></p>\n<h2>Discernment in those who govern</h2>\n<p>Joseph:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:39\">GEN 41:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:10\">ACT 7:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:12\">1KI 3:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:12\">2CH 2:12</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job12:20\">JOB 12:20</a> <em>elders</em></p>\n<h2>Examples of spiritual discernment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:9\">2KI 4:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:19\">JHN 4:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:42\">JHN 4:42</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:19-1Kgs22:23\">1KI 22:19–22:23</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr18:18-2Chr18:22\">2CH 18:18–18:22</a> <em>Micaiah discerns that a lying spirit is responsible for false prophecy.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:16-Jer23:22\">JER 23:16–23:22</a> <em>Jeremiah knows that the false prophets' message is not from God</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:3\">ACT 5:3</a> <em>Peter is aware of the deception of Ananias and Sapphira</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:23\">ACT 8:23</a> <em>Peter discerns the true condition of Simon's heart</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:18\">ACT 16:18</a> <em>Paul discerns the spiritual source of a girl's fortune-telling ability.</em></p>\n<h2>Futher examples of discernment</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam14:18-2Sam14:20\">2SA 14:18–14:20</a> <em>David sees through Joab's ruse</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:24-1Kgs3:28\">1KI 3:24–3:28</a> <em>Solomon discerns a child's true mother</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh6:12-Neh6:13\">NEH 6:12–6:13</a> <em>Nehemiah sees through the plot against him.</em></p>\n<h2>Lack of discernment</h2>\n<h3>Young children lack discernment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:39\">DEU 1:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:15-Isa7:16\">ISA 7:15–7:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah4:11\">JON 4:11</a></p>\n<h3>Israel's lack of discernment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:28\">DEU 32:28</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:54-Luke12:56\">LUK 12:54–12:56</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:3\">ISA 1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:13\">ISA 5:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:18-Isa44:19\">ISA 44:18–44:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek12:2\">EZK 12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:27\">ACT 28:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:9-Isa6:10\">ISA 6:9–6:10</a></p>\n<h3>Those who lack judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:32\">PRO 6:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:21\">PRO 10:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:7\">PRO 7:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov9:4\">PRO 9:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:11\">PRO 12:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:1\">PRO 18:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:30\">PRO 24:30</a></p>\n<h3>Other examples of lack of discernment</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps82:5\">PSA 82:5</a> <em>the “gods” in the heavenly assembly</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:12\">MIC 4:12</a> <em>the nations who fail to discern God's plan</em></p>",
